OL,3,CDad of former Muckamore patient hopes
OL,4,Cinquiry changes safeguarding for good
OL,6,FThe final day of hearings in the
OL,7,FMuckamore Abbey Hospital Inquiry has
OL,8,Fheard that families gave their
OL,9,Fvulnerable relatives "a voice they
OL,10,Fwould not otherwise have had."
OL,12,FAfter two years and nine moths, oral
OL,13,Fevidence from almost 90 witnesses and
OL,14,Fhundreds of thousands of pages of
OL,15,Fmaterial, it is now over to the Chair
OL,16,Fof the Inquiry, Tom Kark KC, to
OL,17,Fproduce recommendations.
OL,19,FHe said he hopes to have presented his
OL,20,Freport to the Health Minister "by the
OL,21,Fend of the year."
