OL,3,CDad of former Muckamore patient hopes
OL,4,Cinquiry changes safeguarding for good
OL,6,F"By giving evidence, the relatives of
OL,7,Fpatients in Muckamore gave their loved
OL,8,Fones a voice they would not otherwise
OL,9,Fhave had," said Mr Kark.
OL,11,F"The evidence they gave was crucial to
OL,12,Fthe understanding of the panel and we
OL,13,Frecognise that for many, probably all,
OL,14,Fthe experience of giving evidence was
OL,15,Fitself very difficult.
OL,17,F"Further, for others just listening to
OL,18,Fthe accounts of the patient
OL,19,Fexperience, the evidence which they
OL,20,Fheard must have been very harrowing
OL,21,Ffor many of them."
