OL,6,FMr Brown has been critical of what the
OL,7,Finquiry might be able to achieve,
OL,8,Fbecause of the ongoing police
OL,9,Finvestigation.
OL,11,F"We would definitely be of the opinion
OL,12,Fthat you don't do anything to
OL,13,Fprejudice the ongoing police
OL,14,Finvestigations," he said.
OL,16,F"But obviously a lot of evidence is
OL,17,Fnot before the public, for justifiable
OL,18,Freasons in some cases, which means the
OL,19,Fpublic will have a totally distorted
OL,20,Fview of what we're complaining about -
OL,21,Fthat's our worry."
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G6/14
