OL,3,CDad of former Muckamore patient hopes
OL,4,Cinquiry changes safeguarding for good
OL,6,F"It may not be sufficient, but it is
OL,7,Fnonetheless important and appropriate
OL,8,Fthat the health and social care
OL,9,Forganisation responsible for the
OL,10,Fhospital in which its patients were
OL,11,Fabused and the abuse was carried out
OL,12,Fby staff employed by the health and
OL,13,Fsocial care organisation, that the
OL,14,Forganisation does say sorry."
OL,16,FThe Department of Health also said
OL,17,Fthat the families were "undoubtedly
OL,18,Ffailed".
OL,20,FA separate criminal probe continues.
